pros:
Very structured career path, you have clear understanding what you will be in next couple of years if everything goes well;
Clear responsibilities at each level, but definitely allow extra responsibility if you proved to be good;
On the way to become a technology smart company, the cooporetation with Google will have further effect;
People are nice and very friendly, not much office politics.

cons:
pay is not attractive, especially at junior level;
It seems the compensation is only differentiated by the level, not the roles. Some roles by nature require people with advanced degree, but pay will be the same with others. Will be hard to retain good people;
All my pros above depends on the team, culture could be different among different teams under different bosses, so in some sense it is by luck.

- Bad environment;
- Top management absent, useless, stubborn and clearly lacking of the most basic management skills;
- Lack of Work-Life balance;
- Promotion, salaries and bonuses are decided by partners just for politically reasons; 
- The assistants and consultants do boring and useless job having nothing to do with the tax matters;

